Module Basics
Package basics.util

Class DoubleArrayList

java.lang.Object
basics.util.DoubleArrayList
public class DoubleArrayList
extends java.lang.Object
In principle, an ArrayList<Double>, but it is much more memory efficient. The Double values are stored into double[], thus mainly the values are stored and not the references to Double objects. Thus, many million values can be stored withouth dealing with memory effects. Some differences to ArrayList<Double>
  • it cannot store null values
  • it is not a subclass of AbstractList
  • some methods are not implemented, e.g. removeAll, iterator
  • some methods exist beyond the ArrayList, e.g. max, min, sort
  • no range checks in the borders of the current array capacity
Author:
Jörg Roth (Joerg.Roth@Wireless-earth.org)
